Gathering some links for the benefit of people who want to check-in changes to vanilla Emacs.

* [http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-faq.html#AssignCopyright  Why assign copyright]
* [http://www.gnu.org/prep/maintain/html_node/Copyright-Papers.html Copyright papers]
* [http://git.savannah.gnu.org/gitweb/?p=gnulib.git;a=tree;f=doc/Copyright;hb=HEAD How the papers look]
* [https://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/manual/html_node/emacs/Copyright-Assignment.html Copyright Assignment in Emacs Manual]
* [http://bzr.savannah.gnu.org/lh/emacs/trunk/annotate/head:/etc/CONTRIBUTE etc/CONTRIBUTE] under [DataDirectory etc/] of Emacs distribution.  (C-h v data-directory for locating DataDirectory).


Insistent of Assignment of rights is met with mixed reaction in general.

* [http://twit.tv/floss117 FLOSS weekly podcast] has some good reasons why getting the copyright registered is important and useful.

See also 

* EmacsSchism
* [https://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/emacs-devel/2013-03/msg00228.html Selective withholding of assignments] and a followup  [https://lwn.net/Articles/543339/ LWN article]


